  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pogo Park: Renewing Richmond&apos;s Elm Playlot</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There are 56 city parks in Richmond, CA, but many of them are rarely used, and their hard-packed earth, decaying rubbish, broken glass, and abandoned needles repel even the most enthusiastic children. But the children of Richmond&apos;s Iron Triangle, like children everywhere, need to play. Our mission is to work with  community residents to transform a local park, the Elm Playlot, into a community hub, a place that is safe, welcoming, and fun, staffed by trained residents who serve as Park Hosts.</narrative>
  </description>
